## Quick start

Requires **Python 3.10+**.

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python server.py
```

> Prefer packaging? `pip install -e .` also works (uses `pyproject.toml`), but
> requires a recent `pip`/`setuptools`.

